OL,3,C'Close to life support': hospitality
OL,4,Cbusinesses urgent plea for help
OL,6,FAt Spanish restaurant Lunya in
OL,7,FLiverpool, owner Peter Kinsella says
OL,8,Fhis energy costs have gone through the
OL,9,Froof: "A few years ago I was paying
OL,10,F#57,000 a year for energy, now it's
OL,11,Fcloser to #250,000.
OL,13,F"It's a massive price increase -
OL,14,Fthat's pretty much four and a half
OL,15,Ftimes what we used to spend."
OL,17,FPeter has been running Lunya for 14
OL,18,Fyears. He says 2023 is his worst year
OL,19,Fyet.
