OL,3,C'Close to life support': hospitality
OL,4,Cbusinesses urgent plea for help
OL,6,FGreens in Didsbury had been a
OL,7,Ffavourite with local people for 33
OL,8,Fyears.
OL,10,FThe popular dining spot opened in the
OL,11,Fcentre of in 1990, but on 2 January a
OL,12,Fstatement on its website titled "Our
OL,13,Fhearts are broken" announced its
OL,14,Fclosure.
OL,16,FSimon said the closure is
OL,17,F"heartbreaking", because the
OL,18,Frestaurant is "still busy, it just
OL,19,Fcan't make enough money, or any money,
OL,20,Freally."
